[{"id":"VR804046","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Solenoid <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> is made of a coil of wire of resistivity <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"rho\"><math alttext=\"rho\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>ρ</mi></math></span></span>. The two ends of the solenoid are connected to a battery of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"e m f\"><math alttext=\"e m f\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>emf</mi></math></span></span> <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open E\"><math alttext=\"open E\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>Ɛ</mi></math></span></span>. When there is a steady current in the solenoid, the magnetic field stores energy <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"U sub 0\"><math alttext=\"U sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span>. Solenoid <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> is made of the same type of wire, has the same number of coils per unit length, and has the same cross-sectional area as Solenoid <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>. Solenoid <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> is twice the length of Solenoid <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>. Solenoid <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> is disconnected from the battery and Solenoid <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> is connected to the same battery. How much energy is stored in Solenoid <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> when there is a steady current in Solenoid <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR804046_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction U sub 0 over 2\"><math alttext=\"the fraction U sub 0 over 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"U sub 0\"><math alttext=\"U sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 U sub 0\"><math alttext=\"2 U sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 U sub 0\"><math alttext=\"4 U sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":0}]